::Shadow Wing::

She was racing for her life.  She dodged and swerved to miss the ice 
formations.  She was feeling fear again.  She rarely felt this emotion.  She 
felt one other time.  That when Lunarpine scared her.  She shook her head.  
She had to think straight in order to keep ahead of this predacon trying to 
kill her. How did he track me, she thought. She knew she had done a good job 
of hiding her scent and flying out of most scanner ranges.  But somehow, 
this pred found her.  She flew up into the sky.  The wind had picked up and 
was blowing harder than before.  The north to south wind was cold and 
strong.  She had an urge to fly back to the Maximal base.  she started to 
fly in that direction and then stopped.  She knew that she couldn't go back. 
Her spark fell for a moment as she hovered and looked to the south. She flew 
Westward, hoping to evade the Pred.  She beat her wings as fast as they 
would go.
She was breathing hard now and she sould see her breath as she flew.  A gust 
of wind caught her and she tumbled a bit in the air.  She regained her 
control and kept flying.
